Giving general feedback is a bit daunting for the average anon most of us don't know where to begin.
It's easier when an author asks about a specific aspect of a story.

Criticizing 'greens' is a bit awkward since the format itself hardly lends itself to HighLiterature(tm), so criticizing form seems redundant, though it's easier to do for those writefags that use a more conventional format.

Also, most of the time people are not in a mindset that lends itself to critique while reading entertaining shorts on the net. Casual critique is something that people can do only after having read a lot and these days few people are proper 'readers' due to distraction from other media. I myself can only really do it with the SciFi/Fantasy aspects of a story since that has been my main reading material for the past 20 years.

Speaking of:
>>11402196
In the 'Speed Mating' story I would argue the use of makeup is inappropriate to a non human species. Makeup is supposed to enhance secondary sexual signals. While use of some sort of eyeliner or mascara would be something likely common in most mammals since most species seem to associate large eyes with youth and vitality (one of the reasons all young animals are seen as cute), stuff like lipstick would be redundant (in some cases you are litteraly putting it on a horse). An anthropomorphic animal would likely put much more emphasis on something like general grooming, good hair/fur conditioner or even nose moisturizer.

I can go at length into insignificant details like that, but on other aspects of a story I'm numb.
